# Typography

**Figma:** [Foundations – Typography](https://www.figma.com/design/AW4jk9SLPKlSqYt6NZ1QK5/Qure-%3C%3E-Figma-Design-system?node-id=9762-187&p=f&m=dev)

Font family, sizes, weights, line heights, and semantic variants below are derived from Figma foundations node 9762:187.

---

## Variables (from design-system-tokens.mdc)

| Use | Token |
|-----|-------|
| Font family | `--font-family` (IBM Plex Sans) |
| Sizes | `--text-xs` through `--text-6xl` |
| Weights | `--font-regular`, `--font-medium`, `--font-semibold`, `--font-bold` |
| Line heights | `--leading-tight`, `--leading-snug`, `--leading-normal`, `--leading-relaxed` |
| Text colors | `--text-base-default`, `--text-base-secondary`, `--text-disabled-default` |

---

## Semantic variants

Prefer semantic variants over raw sizes:

| Variant | Use |
|---------|-----|
| display | Hero, marketing headlines |
| h1–h6 | Section headings |
| body | Paragraphs, content |
| caption | Supporting text, labels |
| overline | Category labels, small caps |

Map to tokens: size, line-height, weight from design-system-tokens.mdc.

---

## Truncation

- Ellipsis when overflow.
- Define max-width per context.

---

## Implementation guidelines

- Use tokens from `design-system-tokens.mdc` only.
- Do not invent variants; implement only what exists in Figma node 9762:187.
